00:38:14,750 --> 00:38:15,960
乔治
George.

569
00:38:16,710 --> 00:38:19,960
这些爆炸物意味着紧迫的威胁
Those explosives mean there is an imminent threat

570
00:38:20,040 --> 00:38:22,250
会对平均人口造成严重伤害
of serious harm to the civilian population.

571
00:38:22,710 --> 00:38:23,710
我们能袭击吗？
Can we strike?

572
00:38:23,800 --> 00:38:27,470
那个，考虑到新出现的情况，我会说，同意
Well, given the new circumstances, I would say yes.

573
00:38:27,550 --> 00:38:28,550
布莱恩
Brian.

574
00:38:30,010 --> 00:38:33,180
我们必须先打一通政治电话和法律电话
There is a political as well as a legal call to be made here.

575
00:38:33,270 --> 00:38:34,850
是的，乔治，我意识到了
Yes, I'm quite aware of that, George.

576
00:38:34,930 --> 00:38:37,940
首相，我们现在就需要一个决定
We need a decision now, Minister.

577
00:38:43,400 --> 00:38:44,820
法律上，我们没有问题吗？
Legally, we don't have a problem?

578
00:38:44,900 --> 00:38:45,940
是的，没有
No, we don't.

579
00:38:46,030 --> 00:38:47,070
但政治上…
But politically...

580
00:38:47,150 --> 00:38:48,410
是否允许我们进行？
Do we have permission to proceed?

581
00:38:51,740 --> 00:38:52,740
那个
Well,

582
00:38:53,910 --> 00:38:55,950
- 乔治，你似乎在暗示“是”  - 谢谢
you seem to be implying yes, George. Thank you.

583
00:38:56,080 --> 00:38:58,120
- 稍等，等一下  - 不，我不是那意思…
Hold on a minute. Hold on. No. That is not what I...

584
00:38:58,870 --> 00:39:02,920
这是抓捕任务转变为了击杀任务，对吗？
This is a change of mission from a capture to a shoot-to-kill, isn't it?

585
00:39:06,050 --> 00:39:07,380
是的，没错
Yes, it is.

586
00:39:07,470 --> 00:39:08,590
我们这么做没问题吗？
Are we all right with that?

587
00:39:09,180 --> 00:39:10,300
我确定这样是有问题的
I'm sure we are not.

588
00:39:10,390 --> 00:39:13,220
目标是两名英国公民和一个美国公民
There are two British citizens and an American as targets.

589
00:39:13,310 --> 00:39:14,720
此次任务已经得到了
This mission has the full support

590
00:39:14,850 --> 00:39:16,220
肯尼亚和美国的全力支持
of Kenya and the United States.

591
00:39:16,310 --> 00:39:17,480
无人机袭击？
For a drone strike?

592
00:39:17,560 --> 00:39:19,020
对，“收割者”上的导弹
Yes, a missile fired from an RPA

593
00:39:19,100 --> 00:39:20,900
就是作为出现这种情况的
is part of an agreed contingency plan

594
00:39:20,980 --> 00:39:22,480
应急计划的一部分
in circumstances like this.

595
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:23,860
我们能够进行攻击？
Do we have permission to proceed?

596
00:39:23,940 --> 00:39:26,860
不，这种计划在没有得到国会的授权前
No. Such a plan should not have been signed off by the PM

597
00:39:26,940 --> 00:39:28,110
首相是不能授权的
without the authority of Parliament.

598
00:39:28,200 --> 00:39:31,370
战略操作本来通常就不在内阁进行讨论
Operational issues are not generally discussed at Cabinet,

599
00:39:31,450 --> 00:39:32,620
毫无疑问，也不会在国会讨论
and certainly not at Parliament.

600
00:39:32,700 --> 00:39:35,870
我很清楚草案，我说的是应该怎么做
I know the protocol. I'm talking about what should be happening.

601
00:39:35,950 --> 00:39:38,410
安吉拉，在我看来，对于一次袭击来说
Angela, in my view, all the legal criteria

602
00:39:38,500 --> 00:39:40,210
它已经符合了所有法律要件
for an attack have been met.

603
00:39:40,290 --> 00:39:43,340
也就是说，这是军事需要
Namely, this is a military necessity,

604
00:39:43,420 --> 00:39:45,670
没有其他合理的选择
there is no reasonable alternative,

605
00:39:45,750 --> 00:39:49,300
而且我们被迫消除威胁
and the force to be used is in proportion to the threat.

606
00:39:49,380 --> 00:39:50,720
这么说，应该解决了你的疑问
That should answer your question.

607
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:52,090
并没有，乔治
It does not, George.

608
00:39:52,180 --> 00:39:55,430
历史上曾经有过一艘由英国驾驶的无人机袭击一个
Has there ever been a British-led drone attack on a city

609
00:39:55,510 --> 00:39:58,100
未在交战中的友国的城市？
in a friendly country that is not at war?

610
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:03,770
上将？
General?

611
00:40:06,480 --> 00:40:08,400
我想没有，是的
I do not believe so, no.

612
00:40:08,490 --> 00:40:09,820
那我们怎么能认可它？
Then how can we sanction it?

613
00:40:12,450 --> 00:40:14,370
重新生成这些无人机上的导弹
Generate new damage rings for the compound

614
00:40:14,450 --> 00:40:16,910
所形成的破坏圈
with an assessment of the payload on those jackets.

615
00:40:16,990 --> 00:40:18,910
- 是，长官  - 立刻
Yes, ma'am. Right now.

616
00:40:25,500 --> 00:40:27,170
- 沃什上校  - 上校
- Colonel Walsh. - Colonel.

617
00:40:28,130 --> 00:40:29,840
我能直接和你的飞行员通话吗？
Can I speak to your pilot directly?

618
00:40:32,970 --> 00:40:35,300
是的，长官，帮我接线
Yes, ma'am. Patch me through.

619
00:40:38,890 --> 00:40:39,890
史蒂夫
Steve.

620
00:40:40,350 --> 00:40:43,020
鲍威尔上校想和你直接谈谈，接吧
Colonel Powell wants to talk to you directly. Pick up.

621
00:40:47,190 --> 00:40:48,360
长官
Ma'am.

622
00:40:48,530 --> 00:40:49,610
中尉
Lieutenant.

623
00:40:49,690 --> 00:40:52,950
你现在是我们消灭这些难题的最佳选择
You are now our best option to take these HVIs out.

624
00:40:53,410 --> 00:40:56,870
现在，准备发射一枚AGM-14“狱火”导弹
Now, prepare to launch a single AGM-114 Hellfire

625
00:40:56,950 --> 00:40:57,950
到目标房屋
on the target house.

626
00:40:59,490 --> 00:41:01,580
- 是，长官  - 这是一个友国城市
Yes, ma'am. This is a friendly city,

627
00:41:01,660 --> 00:41:04,250
所以，附带损害必须降至最低
so collateral damage must be kept to a minimum.

628
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:07,290
- 长官…  - 什么？
Ma'am... Yes?

629
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:09,630
我有一个ROE问题
I have an ROE question.

630
00:41:10,130 --> 00:41:11,720
我们的政府是否知道
Is my government aware that we are

631
00:41:11,800 --> 00:41:13,800
我们正在把一个持美国护照的人作为目标？
targeting a person with a US passport?

632
00:41:15,590 --> 00:41:17,180
是的，是的，中尉
Yes. Yes, it is, Lieutenant.

633
00:41:17,640 --> 00:41:20,020
我在SPINS上，什么也没看到
I didn't see anything in the SPINS about that.

634
00:41:20,100 --> 00:41:21,850
中尉，我们已经有了新的交战规则
Lieutenant, we have new rules of engagement.

635
00:41:21,930 --> 00:41:23,060
你是受保护的
You are covered.

636
00:41:23,560 --> 00:41:25,810
动作必须快，所以准备好投弹吧
This is going to happen fast, so be ready to shoot.

637
00:41:25,900 --> 00:41:27,270
是，长官
Yes, ma'am.

638
00:41:29,570 --> 00:41:31,230
正在检查三十四项清单
Running the dash 34 checklist.

639
00:41:34,240 --> 00:41:35,910
卡莉，准备好了就呼叫我
Carrie, call when ready.

640
00:41:36,030 --> 00:41:37,700
你以前有发射过狱火吗？
You ever shot a Hellfire?

641
00:41:38,990 --> 00:41:40,040
没有
No.

642
00:41:41,580 --> 00:41:42,910
其他弹药呢？
Or anything?

643
00:41:43,910 --> 00:41:46,670
没有，我只当了一年天眼
No. I've only ever been the eye.

644
00:41:48,380 --> 00:41:49,420
你呢？
You?

645
00:41:49,920 --> 00:41:51,170
我也没有
Me, too.

646
00:41:51,760 --> 00:41:53,920
伙计们，看来今天是你们的幸运日
Looks like it's your lucky day today, guys.

647
00:41:54,050 --> 00:41:56,180
保持冷静，好吗？谨慎点
Just stay cool, okay? Be all right.

648
00:41:56,260 --> 00:41:57,300
是，长官
Yes, sir.

649
00:41:57,720 --> 00:41:59,300
卡莉，准备好了就呼叫
Carrie, call when ready.

650
00:42:00,850 --> 00:42:03,350
倾斜范围二点二万英尺
Slant range 22,000 feet.

651
00:42:04,350 --> 00:42:06,020
高冲击角
High-impact angle.

652
00:42:06,770 --> 00:42:08,480
准备好目标简报
Stand by for targeting brief.

653
00:42:08,560 --> 00:42:09,650
准备
Ready.

654
00:42:11,360 --> 00:42:14,490
安吉拉，我同意我们有被视为是
Angela, I agree, we are at risk of being perceived

655
00:42:14,570 --> 00:42:16,860
在从事击杀政策的风险
as embarking on a shoot-to-kill policy.

656
00:42:16,950 --> 00:42:19,700
但既然所有的法律条件都充分
But since all the legal criteria are sound,

657
00:42:19,780 --> 00:42:22,200
我确定，我们必须允许继续这项军事行动
I believe we must allow this military action to continue.

658
00:42:22,290 --> 00:42:23,370
法律上我们也许是安全的
Legally we may be safe,

659
00:42:23,450 --> 00:42:25,210
但政治上，我们这好比是在越雷池
but politically we're walking into a minefield.

660
00:42:25,290 --> 00:42:27,290
尤其是里面还包含了一名美国公民
Especially with an American citizen involved.

661
00:42:27,370 --> 00:42:29,170
首相，是否允许？
Do I have permission, Minister?

662
00:42:31,550 --> 00:42:32,590
呃…
Um...

663
00:42:36,800 --> 00:42:40,930
考虑到这个情况，这是任务转变
Given the situation, that it is a change of mission,

664
00:42:42,510 --> 00:42:46,350
现在成了用导弹袭击英国目标
that it is now a missile attack on a British subject,

665
00:42:46,430 --> 00:42:49,480
两名英国目标，和一名美国公民
two British subjects, and an American citizen,

666
00:42:50,360 --> 00:42:52,070
而且是在一个友国
and in a friendly country,

667
00:42:54,990 --> 00:42:56,360
我认为唯一合理的做法是
I think it is only right and proper

668
00:42:56,440 --> 00:42:58,820
向外交部长上报
that I refer this up to the Foreign Secretary.

669
00:42:59,950 --> 00:43:03,700
首相，刚才的争论你听见了，而他没听见
Minister, you've heard the arguments, he hasn't.

670
00:43:03,790 --> 00:43:05,750
而且交战规则意味着
And the rules of engagement mean that

671
00:43:05,830 --> 00:43:07,960
首相已经认可了它
the Prime Minister has already approved it.

672
00:43:08,040 --> 00:43:09,040
- 不…  - 因此
No... Therefore,

673
00:43:09,120 --> 00:43:11,420
外交部长无需提出意见
the Foreign Secretary's input should not be rendered...

674
00:43:11,500 --> 00:43:14,460
不，重点是我之前没有参与
No, the point is that I have not been party

675
00:43:14,550 --> 00:43:16,720
任何与首相的
to any previous discussion with the Prime Minister

676
00:43:16,800 --> 00:43:18,550
关于此类事件的讨论
about matters such as this,

677
00:43:18,630 --> 00:43:20,970
反之，外交部长是肯定参与了的
whereas the Foreign Secretary undoubtedly has.

678
00:43:23,050 --> 00:43:25,270
所以，向他上报是我的义务
So, actually, it is my duty to refer to him.

679
00:43:25,350 --> 00:43:26,560
那我怎么回复鲍威尔上校？
And what am I telling Colonel Powell?

680
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:27,810
让她等！
Tell her to wait!

681
00:43:35,950 --> 00:43:38,190
我的苍天！
Oh, Christ Almighty!

682
00:43:38,570 --> 00:43:39,610
新加坡，国际武器贸易展销会
谢谢
Thank you.

683
00:43:40,320 --> 00:43:41,870
作为英国政府的成员
As a member of the British government,

684
00:43:41,950 --> 00:43:45,330
我很自豪地向大家介绍综合战场解决方案
I am proud to introduce Integrated Battlefield Solutions,

685
00:43:45,580 --> 00:43:48,000
一家英国公司带领了生产
a UK company leading the field in the production

686
00:43:48,080 --> 00:43:51,040
自救，轻型的军事服装领域
of life-saving, lightweight military clothing.

687
00:43:52,380 --> 00:43:55,630
在战场上保护我们的士兵
Protecting our soldiers in the field of battle

688
00:43:55,710 --> 00:43:57,420
是我们政府对我们的军队
is at the core of my government's

689
00:43:57,550 --> 00:43:59,260
恪守的核心
commitment to our armed forces.

690
00:43:59,760 --> 00:44:03,180
“士兵安全第一” 就是我们为什么在…
"Soldier safety first" is why we 're in...

691
00:44:04,260 --> 00:44:05,390
抱歉
Excuse me.

692
00:44:08,430 --> 00:44:09,980
天呐，他要吐了！
Oh, God, he's gonna throw up!

693
00:44:10,560 --> 00:44:12,520
我早跟他说，别吃大虾了
I told him not to eat the prawns.

694
00:44:12,600 --> 00:44:13,900
抱歉
Excuse me.

695
00:44:14,560 --> 00:44:19,190
很高兴向大家介绍IBS的常务董事
And so I'm very pleased to introduce you to IBS Managing Director.

696
00:44:19,280 --> 00:44:20,740
奈杰尔·阿德勒先生
Mr. Nigel Adler.

697
00:44:22,410 --> 00:44:23,570
非常感谢，外交部长
Thank you very much, Foreign Secretary.

698
00:44:24,410 --> 00:44:27,370
今天我们要介绍坚固的防弹衣系统
Today we're introducing the Adamant Assault Body Armor System.

699
00:44:27,450 --> 00:44:29,410
- 我们收到CDE了没？  - 是的，长官
Do we have that CDE yet? Yes, ma'am.

700
00:44:29,910 --> 00:44:31,120
很好
Good.

701
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:37,170
如果我们以角落的这个房间为目标，也就是爆炸物的所在位置
If we target this corner room here, where the explosives are,

702
00:44:37,250 --> 00:44:40,550
那个房间将发生百分百的死亡率
we would expect 100% mortality rate in that room

703
00:44:40,630 --> 00:44:44,090
而其他房间的死亡率，则在百分之八十到百分之九十
and an 80 to 90% rate within the rest of the house.

704
00:44:45,100 --> 00:44:46,390
集市是安全的
The market should be safe,

705
00:44:47,260 --> 00:44:50,020
但街上的这片区域
but this area here in the street...

706
00:44:50,100 --> 00:44:52,520
死亡率是百分之六十五到百分之七十五
A 65 to 75% rate.

707
00:44:52,600 --> 00:44:54,190
那就是狱火的武力
That's just the Hellfire.

708
00:44:54,270 --> 00:44:56,400
如果我们将爆炸背心计算在内
If we factor in the explosives in the vests,

709
00:44:56,480 --> 00:45:00,280
那这片区域的损害范围将更大
we're looking at even more extensive damage way out to this area here.

710
00:45:00,360 --> 00:45:03,450
但我无法精确计算那个范围
But I can't accurately estimate that yield.

711
00:45:03,950 --> 00:45:06,070
但我们要包括那屋里
But we would be containing that payload in the vests

712
00:45:06,160 --> 00:45:07,450
背心里的弹药，对吗？
within those walls, right?

713
00:45:08,580 --> 00:45:09,620
附加损害远远达不到
Far less collateral damage

714
00:45:09,700 --> 00:45:11,790
伤害集市里的人群
than them going off in a crowded shopping mall.

715
00:45:12,330 --> 00:45:13,500
是的，没错
Yes. Of course.

716
00:45:13,620 --> 00:45:14,830
对，谢谢
Yeah. Thank you.

717
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:17,960
显然，没有人在避免做出决定
Obvious to anyone not trying to avoid making a decision.

718
00:45:23,510 --> 00:45:26,390
和马来西亚贸易部长的会议在四点半
The meeting with the Malaysian Trade Minister is now at 4:30.

719
00:45:26,470 --> 00:45:28,220
你得替我去了
You'll have to do it for me.

720
00:45:28,300 --> 00:45:30,100
但是，先生，我们来这的整个重点是…
But, sir, the whole point of us being here...

721
00:45:30,180 --> 00:45:31,640
对，也许你可以吃片抗过敏药
Yeah, maybe if you take an Eezi Tum.

722
00:45:31,730 --> 00:45:34,690
听着，我现在必须回酒店
Look. I need to go back to the hotel now.

723
00:45:39,320 --> 00:45:40,480
杰克，这交通阻塞是怎么回事？
Jack, what's the holdup?

724
00:45:40,570 --> 00:45:42,440
抱歉，先生，我已经在尽力联系他了
I'm sorry, sir, I'm trying to reach him.

725
00:45:42,530 --> 00:45:44,740
首相，拖延决定
Minister, the consequences of delay

726
00:45:44,860 --> 00:45:47,070
也许对大量市民们来说是致命的
may be fatal to scores of civilians.

727
00:45:47,160 --> 00:45:48,620
上将，我很清楚这点
I'm well aware of that, General,

728
00:45:48,700 --> 00:45:51,410
但得到他的认可，对我来说，是合理程序
but it is the proper procedure for me to seek his approval.

729
00:45:51,490 --> 00:45:54,250
如果这些人现在分开乘坐汽车离开
If these men leave now, in separate vehicles...

730
00:45:54,330 --> 00:45:55,670
那外面停了两辆车
There are two vehicles outside,

731
00:45:55,750 --> 00:45:57,790
我们只有能力跟踪一辆
we have the ability to follow only one.

732
00:45:57,880 --> 00:45:59,750
我们只有一个天眼
We have only one eye in the sky.

733
00:45:59,840 --> 00:46:01,800
你在地面上的特工们应该可以拦截吧？
Surely you have agents on the ground who could intercept?

734
00:46:02,670 --> 00:46:04,840
拦截城市街头的自杀炸弹袭击者？
Intercept a suicide bomber on a city street?

735
00:46:04,920 --> 00:46:07,050
我们是想最大程度的减少附带损伤
We're trying to minimize collateral damage.

736
00:46:07,340 --> 00:46:09,100
肖曼5-0，北2-0
Showman 5-0, North 2-0.

737
00:46:09,510 --> 00:46:11,010
我发出攻击命令后，你必须
When I give the order to attack, you have to

738
00:46:11,180 --> 00:46:12,640
让你的人立即离开
get your man out of there immediately.

739
00:46:12,720 --> 00:46:14,230
我们大概三分钟就会到达
He'll have about three minutes.

740
00:46:14,310 --> 00:46:15,690
明白
Understood.

741
00:46:48,550 --> 00:46:51,600
我们一切正常，导弹状态稳定
We are greened up. Missile status is ready.

